						               													<description>Each player begins with $300, a delivery truck to be used as a pawn, and eight cones which match the color of the delivery truck chosen. The truck begins the game on the corner of the matching color of the game board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turn, a player rolls the six-sided die and moves the delivery truck around the game board clockwise. After following the instructions on the space, a player has five options:&amp;#10;1. Buy ice cream from the bank at the prices printed on the current Inventory Price Card.&amp;#10;2. Sell ice cream back to the bank $100 plus the bonus earned for having chains of shops on the game board.&amp;#10;3. Build one store for $400.&amp;#10;4. Pay a competitor to force a sale of a store from that competitor of $600.&amp;#10;5. Pass.&amp;#10;Play continues until one player can be declared the winner by having eight stores and $3000 in cash.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
